# UI Component Structure Standards

## Purpose
Define folder and file conventions for UI components, screens, and layouts in `src/platform`.
For layer boundaries and runtime behavior, see `platform-ui.mdc`.

## Folder Structure (Authoritative)

Related UIs must be grouped in category folders.

```txt
src/platform/
  components/
    <category>/
      <ComponentName>/
        ComponentName.jsx                     # required shared implementation (default)
        ComponentName.android.jsx             # optional override
        ComponentName.ios.jsx                 # optional override
        ComponentName.web.jsx                 # optional override
        ComponentName.styles.jsx              # required shared styles
        ComponentName.android.styles.jsx      # optional override
        ComponentName.ios.styles.jsx          # optional override
        ComponentName.web.styles.jsx          # optional override
        useComponentName.js                   # optional shared hook
        types.js                              # optional constants/contracts
        index.js                              # barrel (exports only)
  screens/
    <category>/
      <ScreenName>/
        ScreenName.jsx                        # required shared implementation (default)
        ScreenName.android.jsx                # optional override
        ScreenName.ios.jsx                    # optional override
        ScreenName.web.jsx                    # optional override
        ScreenName.styles.jsx                 # required shared styles
        ScreenName.android.styles.jsx         # optional override
        ScreenName.ios.styles.jsx             # optional override
        ScreenName.web.styles.jsx             # optional override
        useScreenName.js                      # optional shared hook
        types.js                              # optional constants/contracts
        index.js                              # barrel (exports only)
```

## Rules

1. Grouping
- All components/screens must be inside category folders (`forms/`, `navigation/`, `auth/`, etc).
- Parentheses folders are never used in `src/platform`.
- Root-level `components/<Name>/` and `screens/<Name>/` are forbidden.

2. Platform Strategy (Shared-First)
- Do not use `Platform.OS` checks in platform UI render files.
- Build shared implementation first in unsuffixed files (`ComponentName.jsx`, `ScreenName.jsx`).
- Add `.android/.ios/.web` files only when behavior or markup truly differs by platform.
- When overrides exist, keep external props/API identical and move shared logic to hooks/helpers.

3. Styles
- Default to shared styles in `*.styles.jsx`.
- Add `*.android.styles.jsx`, `*.ios.styles.jsx`, `*.web.styles.jsx` only for platform-only visual differences.
- Use theme tokens only. No hardcoded visual values.
- `StyleSheet` is allowed only in native override style files for static, token-driven, performance-critical styles.
- Styled-components must be module-level constants in `.styles.jsx` files only.

4. Style Imports
- `*.android.jsx` imports only `*.android.styles.jsx` (or shared `*.styles.jsx` when no override exists).
- `*.ios.jsx` imports only `*.ios.styles.jsx` (or shared `*.styles.jsx` when no override exists).
- `*.web.jsx` imports only `*.web.styles.jsx` (or shared `*.styles.jsx` when no override exists).
- Shared composition is allowed from `*.styles.jsx` into platform override style files.
- Cross-importing one platform override style file into another is forbidden.

5. Logic Placement
- Rendering stays in component/screen files.
- Reusable logic belongs in `useComponentName.js` / `useScreenName.js`.
- Constants/contracts belong in `types.js`.

6. Barrel and Export Pattern
- Barrel files must be `index.js` (never `index.jsx`).
- Primary export pattern:
```js
export { default } from './ComponentName';
```
- Additional exports follow component first, then hook, then constants.

## Naming
- Components/Screens/Layouts: `PascalCase`
- Hooks: `use` + `PascalCase`
- Styles: `[Name].styles.jsx` and optional `[Name].<platform>.styles.jsx`
- Constants/contracts: `types.js`

## Imports
- Prefer alias imports (`@platform/...`) over deep relative paths.
- Outside platform layer, consume through platform barrels whenever available.

## Forbidden
- `Platform.OS` conditionals in platform UI render files
- Unnecessary platform override files when shared implementation is sufficient
- Styled-components outside `.styles.jsx`
- Inline styles for production UI
- Cross-imports between platform override style files
- Duplicated logic/styles across platform files when shared code would work
- Violating category-based folder structure
